About
Drive real earth-moving machines at Dig ThisÂ® Book your choice of any of our machines: our Caterpillar D5K Track-Type Bulldozer, Caterpillar 3I5CL Hydraulic Excavator, Skid Steer, or Mini Excavator. When taking the controls of our massive machines, we want to make sure that you are safe at all times. We start each session with a quick overview of the safety procedures that we require you to follow while digging. After you pass the breathalyzer test, you get fitted for your super-cool neon yellow vest and hardhat! (Beware! Your Dig is non-refundable if you fail the breathalyzer test). Our instructors walk you through every lever, button, and thing-a-majig that you need to know to maneuver our machines with the grace of a ballerina. After just a short time of in-cab training, you'll be Operating like a Pro! Come dressed for the outside conditions and please wear hard soled and closed toed shoes.
Duration: 1-2 hours

Absolutely lived up to my high expectations
Oct 2024 â¢ Solo
I first heard about Dig This over a decade ago, and immediately said "I must do this". If you're the kind of person who is essentially 8 years old when it comes to heavy duty construction equipment, you'll know what I'm talking about. I'm a small woman in my 60's; obviously, this is something that is going to appeal to a lot of age ranges.

This is not a cheap experience, especially if you decide that you want to do both the bulldozer and the excavator. It was absolutely worth the money. Mark, my instructor, was a great cheerleader and instructor. He was patient and upbeat, and had me building dirt piles and excavating holes in no time. Since I was there solo, he kindly took some videos of me driving the 'dozer over the "hill" I'd built. It was wonderful to see what it looked like from the spectator perspective. Sharing that video and my selfies with friends has earned me serious respect! It looked a lot scarier than what it felt like (and I felt entirely safe the entire time).

I finished the too-short experience feeling accomplished, giddy, and grinning ear to ear. Highly, highly recommend.
